%description:
Deterministic MLDv1 host group-state-transition test (RFC 2710 §5).

Exercises the three host states (Non-Listener, Delaying Listener, Idle Listener)
and the four RFC 2710 host behaviors, each proved by Mldv1 EV_INFO markers in stdout.
Membership is driven by real apps (UdpSink with multicastGroup), the production path.

RFC 2710 §5 host state machine (summarized):

  Non-Listener
    |  join (send unsolicited Report, start timer)
    v
  Delaying Listener <-------- General/MAS Query received (start/reset timer)
    |  timer expired (send Report, flag=true)   |  Report received (cancel timer, clear flag)
    v                                            v
  Idle Listener ------- leave (send Done if flag=true) --> Non-Listener

Trajectories tested (both hosts join ff0e::1 on the shared hub segment):

TRAJ-1  ff0e::1  (host1 and host2)
  Non-Listener --> join --> DELAYING_LISTENER (unsolicited Report sent by each host)

  HOST-01: The unsolicited "sending Multicast Listener Report" line from host1
  proves the Non-Listener --> DELAYING_LISTENER transition (join fires Report).

TRAJ-2  ff0e::1  suppression  (host2 hears host1's Report on the shared hub)
  host2 is in DELAYING_LISTENER when it receives host1's Report for ff0e::1.
  host2 cancels its pending timer and transitions --> IDLE_LISTENER without sending
  a second Report (RFC 2710 §5: "cancel timer, clear flag").

  HOST-03: The "received Multicast Listener Report" line from host2
  proves the DELAYING_LISTENER --> IDLE_LISTENER suppression path.

TRAJ-3  ff0e::1  Query-driven  (host1 receives General Query after becoming Idle)
  After host1's initial Report timer fires (Non-Listener --> DELAYING --> IDLE_LISTENER),
  the router's first General Query arrives at t~2s. host1 (now Idle) transitions
  IDLE_LISTENER --> DELAYING_LISTENER and schedules a uniform(0, maxRespDelay) delayed Report.

  HOST-02: The "received General Listener Query" line proves Idle --> DELAYING_LISTENER.
  The subsequent "sending Multicast Listener Report" line proves the delayed Report was sent.

TRAJ-4  ff0e::1  Done on leave  (host1 leaves at t=5s via UdpSink stopTime)
  host1's UdpSink has stopTime=5s. Socket close fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal ->
  Mldv1::multicastGroupLeft -> Done sent to ff02::2.  After the Query-driven Report
  (flag=true), Done is sent to ff02::2 (ALL_ROUTERS_2).

  HOST-04: The "sending Multicast Listener Done" line proves
  IDLE_LISTENER --> NON_LISTENER (leave with Done, flag=true).

Note on intermediate IDLE_LISTENER observability: timer expiry is only EV_DEBUG in Mldv1
(not EV_INFO), so the IDLE_LISTENER state after unsolicited-Report-timer expiry is inferred
from the sequence: (1) join -> unsolicited Report, (2) Query received -> delayed Report
scheduled, (3) delayed Report sent. The presence of (2) proves the host was Idle (not
Delaying) when the Query arrived, confirming the timer-expired transition occurred.

Network: host1, host2, and router all connect to a shared EthernetHub.
Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns /64 link-local and global addresses.
hasMld=true on all nodes; dupAddrDetectTransmits=0 eliminates DAD delay.
Router is a real querier (multicastForwarding=true at node level) with short timers.
seed-set=0 pins uniform(0, maxRespDelay) for deterministic timer behavior.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network MldHostGroupstatesNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        host2: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        host2.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = MldHostGroupstatesNetwork
sim-time-limit = 30s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespTime) in startHostTimer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLD on all nodes
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
# Disable DAD so addresses are available immediately (no ~1s delay before group joins activate)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# TRAJ-1/2/3/4: both hosts join ff0e::1 via UdpSink (real production path).
# Socket join fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> Mldv1::multicastGroupJoined,
# sending an unsolicited Report and starting the Delaying timer.
# Both hosts on the same hub segment means each host's Report is seen by the other,
# enabling TRAJ-2 suppression (host2 hears host1's Report while still Delaying).
**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host1.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1"
# TRAJ-4: host1 leaves at t=5s via socket close (fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal -> Done).
**.host1.app[0].stopTime = 5s

**.host2.numApps = 1
**.host2.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host2.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host2.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1"

# TRAJ-3: real querier on the router drives the Idle -> Delaying -> Report path.
# multicastForwarding MUST be set at node level: NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates
# *.multicastForwarding = this.multicastForwarding to the routing table. A per-submodule
# setting (**.router.ipv6.routingTable.multicastForwarding = true) would be overridden.
**.router.multicastForwarding = true
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 2s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 5s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-01 / TRAJ-1: unsolicited Multicast Listener Report sent by host1 on join, AND
%# HOST-02b / TRAJ-3: query-driven Report sent by host1 after General Query timer fires.
%# Proves both: (a) Non-Listener --> DELAYING_LISTENER (join fires unsolicited Report) and
%#              (b) DELAYING_LISTENER --> IDLE_LISTENER (delayed Report sent after query).
%# Disambiguated by asserting >= 2 host1 Report sends (unsolicited + at least one query-driven).
%# Extracting the 2nd occurrence proves it is independent of the 1st (regression in either path
%# would reduce the count to 1, causing %contains to fail on an empty file).
%postrun-command: grep "MldHostGroupstatesNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1" test.out | sed -n '2p' > host1_report2.out || true
%contains: host1_report2.out
sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-03 / TRAJ-2: report suppression -- host2 hears host1's Report while still in Delaying state
%# Proves: DELAYING_LISTENER --> IDLE_LISTENER via received Report (suppression path) -- input proof
%contains: stdout
MldHostGroupstatesNetwork.host2.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1 iface=eth0

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-03 / TRAJ-2: suppression output proof -- host2 must NOT fire its pending unsolicited-retransmit
%# timer before the first General Query.  After host2 sends its join-time unsolicited Report and
%# then receives host1's Report on the shared hub, Mldv1 must call cancelEvent(timer) on the
%# retransmit timer.  If that cancelEvent were missing, the timer would fire and a second
%# "sending Multicast Listener Report" line from host2 would appear before the first General Query.
%# Count host2 Report sends up to (not including) host2's first "received General Listener Query";
%# must be exactly 1 (the join-time unsolicited Report only).
%postrun-command: awk '/MldHostGroupstatesNetwork.host2.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received General Listener Query/{exit} /MldHostGroupstatesNetwork.host2.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1/{count++} END{print count+0}' test.out > host2_suppress_count.out || true
%contains: host2_suppress_count.out
1

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-02a / TRAJ-3: router's General Query received by host1 (host1 is in IDLE_LISTENER at this point)
%# Proves: IDLE_LISTENER --> DELAYING_LISTENER transition (query received schedules delayed Report)
%contains: stdout
MldHostGroupstatesNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received General Listener Query on iface=eth0

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-04 / TRAJ-4: Done sent by host1 at t=5s when UdpSink stopTime fires (flag=true after Query Report)
%# Proves: IDLE_LISTENER --> NON_LISTENER via leave with Done (flag=true path)
%contains: stdout
MldHostGroupstatesNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1 on iface=eth0

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
